Core Projects – C Programming

## Introduction

This section focuses on mini real-world C projects that combine multiple concepts like loops, functions, arrays, strings, file handling (basic), and logic building. These projects help you move from “question solving” to actual software development thinking.

## Topics Covered

Modular programming (functions)
Arrays and strings usage
File handling basics (optional level)
Menu-driven programs
Data storage in memory
Logic building for real applications
Input validation and user interaction

## Core Project

1) Matrix Calculator (2x2 / 3x3)
Perform addition, subtraction, and multiplication of matrices using functions.

2) File Organizer (Basic CLI Tool)
Simulate organizing files into categories based on file extension (like .txt, .c, .jpg).

3) Command-Line Quiz Application
Create a quiz with multiple questions, score calculation, and final result display.

4) Password Generator & Strength Checker
Generate random passwords and evaluate strength based on rules (length, symbols, digits).

5) Number System Converter
Convert numbers between:
Binary ↔ Decimal
Decimal ↔ Hexadecimal

6) Contact Book (Mini Database System)
Store, display, search, and delete contacts using arrays/structures.

7) Advanced Calculator (Menu Driven)
Calculator with options:
+, -, *, /
Power
Square root (basic logic)

8) Text-Based Game (Guess the Number)

Computer generates a number and user has to guess it with hints.
